  "name": "Accustomed to Awfulness",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/skills/green_22.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>At 3rd level, you become immune to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Sickened\">sickened</a>&nbsp;condition and gain a +4 bonus on all&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/combat#TOC-Saving-Throws\">saving throws</a>&nbsp;against effects that cause nausea or&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions#TOC-Diseases\">disease</a>. At 9th level, you become immune to the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/conditions#TOC-Nauseated\">nauseated</a>&nbsp;condition and to the debilitating effects of&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.d20pfsrd.com/gamemastering/afflictions#TOC-Diseases\">disease</a>&nbsp;(but you can still be a carrier of diseases).</p>",
